                       |BKB-= |CKBBack Stab |BKB=-
               
|MKOBackstab is a thief's most powerful skill, one that he
or she learns in the last level of guild experience.
It takes a thief of the utmost dexterity, intelligence,
and strength to find that perfect opening in a target's
exposed back and land a dehabilitating blow. If that
blow is accurate enough, it could bring an opponent
to its knees, rendering it unable to run, and opening
up a window of opportunity for other thieves to 
launch additional assaults on the crippled victim. Only
a thief with comparable or exceeding skill and experience
to the target will effectively be able to stun an opponent 
consistently, but as the brotherhood likes to hunt in
packs, it is not difficult to find thieves from varying
levels of skill.

|WKONOTE: |MKBA thief must be hiding in the shadows to execute this
manuever


|CKOGLVL required: |GKB20
|CKOSyntax: |YKOstab <target>                 |CKOCost: |WKOVaried
